# Implementation Plan: Client State, Updating, and Deletion

This plan handles introducing dynamic database fields to support "Active/Inactive" status filtering, alongside integrating edit and delete functionality for individual clients. 

## User Review Required & Manual Steps
> [!WARNING]
> Because you are using Supabase as your backend, changing the `ClientEntity` properties requires you to update the specific table schema on the database before changes will succeed.
>
> **Action Required to prevent crashes before/after this update**: 
> You must manually add a new column to your `clients` table in Supabase:
> - Name: `is_active`
> - Type: `boolean`
> - Default Value: `true`
> Let me know if you have already done this!

## Proposed Changes

### Domain & Data Updates
#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/client/domain/entities/client_entity.dart`
- Add `@JsonKey(name: 'is_active', defaultValue: true) required bool isActive` to the `ClientEntity` factory.

#### [COMMAND] `dart run build_runner build -d`
- After modifying the entity, I will regenerate the `freezed` and `g.dart` mapping files so `fromJson` and `toJson` capture the new `is_active` field appropriately.

### Presentation Updates
#### [NEW] Local Provider (in `lib/features/client/presentation/providers/client_providers.dart`)
- Define an `enum ClientFilter { all, active, inactive }` and a StateProvider `final clientFilterProvider = StateProvider<ClientFilter>((ref) => ClientFilter.all);` to handle tab filtering.

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/client/presentation/pages/client_dashboard_view.dart`
- Update the layout to use `ref.watch(clientFilterProvider)` to filter the list prior to rendering based on `client.isActive`.
- Update the "Filter Pills" (the 'All', 'Active', 'Inactive' buttons) to switch this internal provider state.
- Add trailing action buttons (an Edit icon and a Delete icon) onto each Client card.
  - Delete will summon a `AlertDialog` confirming they wish to delete, then call the existing `.deleteClient()` hook and invalidate the provider.
  - Edit will launch `AddClientDialog` utilizing its new parameters.

#### [MODIFY] `lib/features/client/presentation/pages/add_client_dialog.dart`
- Update constructor to take `final ClientEntity? clientToEdit;`.
- Use the `initState` to pre-fill controllers.
- Add a new `SwitchListTile` to toggle `isActive` directly from this modal form.
- Use `clientRepository.updateClient()` instead of `.addClient()` if editing.

## Verification Plan
1. Ensure `dart run build_runner build` completes successfully.
2. Confirm the UI compiles without errors via `dart analyze`.
3. Inform user to confirm the schema alteration on Supabase end to ensure real runtime API saves pass!
